The paper deals with a method for segmentation of medical images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The method involves computing a displacement field and utilizing partial volume information, which suggests a possible fit with multimedia (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also mentions the use of a graph-based representation and optimization, which is a common technique in computer science and information science (cs.SI).
